  "prompt": "The income paid/credited showing on my 26AS statement is Rs. 1,25,367.44 (salary income) and on Form 16, the total income shown is Rs 1,33,209 (after deducting PF). Which one should I show in ITR 1 under 'Income from Chargeable Salaries'?",
  "response": "In your case, you should show the amount that appears on **Form 16** under 'Income from Chargeable Salaries' in your ITR-1. Here's why:\n\n1. **Form 16** is issued by your employer and reflects your **gross salary** after permissible deductions like Provident Fund (PF), Professional Tax, etc. It represents the **actual taxable salary** as per the employer's calculations.\n2. **Form 26AS** shows the income (TDS deducted) as reported by your employer to the Income Tax Department. The amount in Form 26AS may not always match Form 16 due to timing differences or adjustments.\n\nSince Form 16 is the **official document** for your salary income, use the amount mentioned in it (**Rs. 1,33,209**) in your ITR-1. This ensures consistency with your employer's records and avoids discrepancies during assessment.\n\nHowever, ensure that the TDS amount in Form 16 matches the TDS credit shown in Form 26AS. If there are any discrepancies, reconcile them with your employer or the tax department before filing your return.",
